				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5158273/scp-3138#post-3699922</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 03 Feb 2018 22:50:13 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>3122708</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>'Corpus Delicti' would have been a good alternate title, but I really wanted that sense of isolation that Poe's poem always gave me.</p> <p>Also: There's a subtle reference there to one of my tales that I don't know if anyone's going to pick up. Seven dead men; four of them Capone's, three of them <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/red-harvest">unidentified</a>.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
